library(ggrepel)

bat_data <- read_csv("dataset/MLB_bat_data_2021.csv")
## Rows: 61316 Columns: 24
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr   (5): game_id, team_abbrev, player_id, player, details
## dbl  (18): ab, r, h, rbi, bb, so, pa, batting_order, doubles, triples, home_...
## date  (1): game_date
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
bat_data_2 <- bat_data %>% select(-game_id, -player_id, -details,
                                  -batting_order, -DKP, -FDP, -SDP) %>%
  mutate(singles = h - (doubles + triples + home_runs),
         tb = singles + 2*doubles + 3*triples + 4*home_runs,
         on_base = h + bb + hit_by_pitch)

bat_data_2 %>% arrange(game_date) %>% group_by(player) %>%
  filter(sum(home_runs) >= 40) %>% mutate(hr = cumsum(home_runs)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = game_date, y = hr, color = player, group = player)) +
  geom_line()

ops_data <- bat_data_2 %>% group_by(player) %>%
  summarize(ab = sum(ab),
            pa = sum(pa),
            tb = sum(tb),
            on_base = sum(on_base)) %>% 
  mutate(obp = on_base/pa, slg = tb/ab, ops = obp + slg) %>% 
  arrange(desc(ops))

ops_data %>% filter(pa >= 500, ops >= .9) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = pa, y = ops)) + geom_point() +
  geom_text_repel(aes(label = player), size = 3) +
  labs(title = ".900+ OPS Hitters vs Plate Appearances",
       x = "Plate Appearances", y = "OPS")

ops_data_month <- bat_data_2 %>% separate(game_date,
                                      into = c("year", "month", "day")) %>% 
  group_by(player, month) %>%
  summarize(ab = sum(ab),
            pa = sum(pa),
            tb = sum(tb),
            on_base = sum(on_base)) %>% 
  mutate(obp = on_base/pa, slg = tb/ab, ops = obp + slg) %>% 
  arrange(desc(ops))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'player'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
ops_data_month %>%
  filter(player %in% filter(ops_data, pa >= 500, ops >= 0.9)$player,
         month != 10) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(month, ops, color = player, group = player)) + geom_point() +
  geom_line()

library(tidyverse)
library(modelr)
library(ggrepel)

stat_fct <- function(x,y){
  ifelse(y > 0, x/y, 0)
}

bat_data <- read_csv("dataset/MLB_bat_data_2021.csv")
## Rows: 61316 Columns: 24
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ","
## chr   (5): game_id, team_abbrev, player_id, player, details
## dbl  (18): ab, r, h, rbi, bb, so, pa, batting_order, doubles, triples, home_...
## date  (1): game_date
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
bat_data_2 <- bat_data %>% select(-game_id, -player_id, -details,
                                  -batting_order, -DKP, -FDP, -SDP) %>%
  mutate(singles = h - (doubles + triples + home_runs),
         tb = singles + 2*doubles + 3*triples + 4*home_runs,
         on_base = h + bb + hit_by_pitch) %>%
  arrange(player, game_date)

ops_data <- bat_data_2 %>% group_by(player) %>%
  summarize(ab = sum(ab),
            pa = sum(pa),
            tb = sum(tb),
            on_base = sum(on_base)) %>% 
  mutate(obp = stat_fct(on_base, pa), slg = stat_fct(tb, ab),
         ops = obp + slg) %>% select(player, obp, slg, ops)

MLB_avg <- bat_data_2 %>%
  summarize(ab = sum(ab),
            pa = sum(pa),
            tb = sum(tb),
            on_base = sum(on_base)) %>% 
  mutate(obp = stat_fct(on_base, pa), slg = stat_fct(tb, ab),
         ops = obp + slg) %>% select(obp, slg, ops)

bat_data_day <- left_join(bat_data_2, ops_data, by = "player")

sim1 <- bat_data_day %>% group_by(player) %>% filter(sum(pa) >= 500) %>%
  group_by(game_date) %>%
  mutate(obp_game = stat_fct(on_base, pa),
         slg_game = stat_fct(tb, ab),
         ops_game = obp_game + slg_game,
         ops_diff = ops_game - MLB_avg$ops,
         above = (ops_diff > 0)) %>% ungroup() %>% group_by(player) %>%
  summarize(games_above = sum(above), ops = mean(ops))
  
model1 <- lm(games_above ~ ops, data = sim1)
(beta <- coef(model1))
## (Intercept)         ops 
##     1.53129    82.67830
ggplot(sim1, aes(ops, games_above)) + geom_point() +
    geom_abline(intercept = beta[1], slope = beta[2])

s_res1 <- rstandard(model1)
sim1 %>% cbind(s_res1) %>%  ggplot(aes(ops, s_res1)) +
  geom_ref_line(h = 0) + geom_point()

sim1 %>% cbind(s_res1) %>% filter(abs(s_res1) >= 2)
##                 player games_above       ops    s_res1
## 36  Fernando Tatis Jr.          70 0.9753475 -2.048300
## 57          Joey Votto          67 0.9377345 -2.015772
## 82       Marcus Semien          86 0.8725977  2.043062
## 102       Ozzie Albies          81 0.7985719  2.221480
## 106      Rafael Devers          89 0.8904807  2.299251
## 118        Tommy Edman          73 0.6936972  2.346065
## 129         Will Smith          60 0.8604385 -2.098578
bat_data_day %>% filter(player == "Rafael Devers") %>%
  group_by(game_date) %>%
  mutate(obp_game = stat_fct(on_base, pa),
         slg_game = stat_fct(tb, ab),
         ops_game = obp_game + slg_game,
         ops_diff = ops_game - ops,
         sign = sign(ops_diff)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(game_date, ops_diff)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = sign), position = "identity", show.legend = FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Rafael Devers Game by Game OPS Data",
       x = "Date", y = "Game OPS compared to average")

bat_data_day %>% filter(player == "Joey Votto") %>%
  group_by(game_date) %>%
  mutate(obp_game = stat_fct(on_base, pa),
         slg_game = stat_fct(tb, ab),
         ops_game = obp_game + slg_game,
         ops_diff = ops_game - ops,
         sign = sign(ops_diff)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(game_date, ops_diff)) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = sign), position = "identity", show.legend = FALSE) +
  labs(title = "Joey Votto Game by Game OPS Data",
       x = "Date", y = "Game OPS compared to average")
